snippet.textDisplay:
Its cool to promote a home workout, I'm all for that... 
However why not just promote the Home Workout without the "fear mongering" rope a dope stuff. I'm way, way, past too logical for the postering of restrictions because of the Coronavirus? 
Are gyms being restricted for real? I'm being serious and I do not know that answer. They aren't here, so?

My big issue with this Coronavirus is simple according to https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/#countries 
USA doesn't even have 5,000 cases nation wide and there have been 72 deaths... Never to dismiss it is not nasty, and it is very sad people died! However over 300,000 people a die from prescription drugs annually (sort of a odd twist but yet)?
One that is more in sync is the flu... what about the 30,000 - 60,000 of people who die from the Flu annually in the USA alone.
On top of that the Coronavirus does not have a long life out in the open... and soap and water kills it if its on your body.
I get that people sneeze and stuff, and thats gross... But carry a napkin and place it in the TRASH not on the ground! 

I went in to Walmart this morning in a Texas town with zero cases of Covid19 and the hand wipes were all over the ground and the dispenser was empty... There was zero toilet paper, zero paper towels, zero Kleenex, zero hand sanitizer, ZERO water, and the list goes on and on... Do you know why this happened? A rumor took off and spread like lighting that there was a confirmed case of Covid19. The city lost its damn mind and emptied the stores... This is what fear mongering does. It causes even more problems.

The news people who do 90% of the fear mongering are now having to try and stop a FAKE PANIC! 
It's really sad to see how freaked out people get, and I guess that is why this just hit me a little wrong.

We should stay healthy, stay clean, carry some Kleenex in our pockets, and go on with LIFE... At this point (and yes that could change) its about as easy to win the lottery, or get struck by lightning, as it is to get the virus (WHICH most people recover from fully by the way).
Sorry to stomp all over the gripey box and kick it over, but good grief... I just needed to let it out I guess.
Have great day, be healthy, and never live in fear.

One more tiny rant... I do see how these "restrictions" can become tools to restrict and take away a whole lot of FREEDOM...
Thats a whole different thing, but its so easy to use and "emergency" to take away more and more freedom... I gotta shut up.
I think I need to go back to bed and wake back up in a better mood... damn. : )
